 2590      // parse patterns, separated by '|' s
 2591      fn parse_pats(&mut self) -> Vec<@Pat> {
 2592          let mut pats = Vec::new();
 2593          loop {
 2594              pats.push(self.parse_pat());
 2595              if self.token == token::BINOP(token::OR) { self.bump(); }
 2596              else { return pats; }
 2597          };
 2598      }
 2599  
 2600      fn parse_pat_vec_elements(
 2601          &mut self,
 2602      ) -> (Vec<@Pat> , Option<@Pat>, Vec<@Pat> ) {
 2603          let mut before = Vec::new();
 2604          let mut slice = None;
 2605          let mut after = Vec::new();
 2606          let mut first = true;
 2607          let mut before_slice = true;
 2608  
 2609          while self.token != token::RBRACKET {
 2610              if first { first = false; }
 2611              else { self.expect(&token::COMMA); }
 2612  
 2613              let mut is_slice = false;
 2614              if before_slice {
 2615                  if self.token == token::DOTDOT {
 2616                      self.bump();
 2617                      is_slice = true;
 2618                      before_slice = false;
 2619                  }
 2620              }
 2621  
 2622              if is_slice {
 2623                  if self.token == token::COMMA || self.token == token::RBRACKET {
 2624                      slice = Some(@ast::Pat {
 2625                          id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2626                          node: PatWildMulti,
 2627                          span: self.span,
 2628                      })
 2629                  } else {
 2630                      let subpat = self.parse_pat();
 2631                      match *subpat {
 2632                          ast::Pat { id, node: PatWild, span } => {
 2633                              self.obsolete(self.span, ObsoleteVecDotDotWildcard);
 2634                              slice = Some(@ast::Pat {
 2635                                  id: id,
 2636                                  node: PatWildMulti,
 2637                                  span: span
 2638                              })
 2639                          },
 2640                          ast::Pat { node: PatIdent(_, _, _), .. } => {
 2641                              slice = Some(subpat);
 2642                          }
 2643                          ast::Pat { span, .. } => self.span_fatal(
 2644                              span, "expected an identifier or nothing"
 2645                          )
 2646                      }
 2647                  }
 2648              } else {
 2649                  let subpat = self.parse_pat();
 2650                  if before_slice {
 2651                      before.push(subpat);
 2652                  } else {
 2653                      after.push(subpat);
 2654                  }
 2655              }
 2656          }
 2657  
 2658          (before, slice, after)
 2659      }

 2661      // parse the fields of a struct-like pattern
 2662      fn parse_pat_fields(&mut self) -> (Vec<ast::FieldPat> , bool) {
 2663          let mut fields = Vec::new();
 2664          let mut etc = false;
 2665          let mut first = true;
 2666          while self.token != token::RBRACE {
 2667              if first {
 2668                  first = false;
 2669              } else {
 2670                  self.expect(&token::COMMA);
 2671                  // accept trailing commas
 2672                  if self.token == token::RBRACE { break }
 2673              }
 2674  
 2675              etc = self.token == token::UNDERSCORE || self.token == token::DOTDOT;
 2676              if self.token == token::UNDERSCORE {
 2677                  self.obsolete(self.span, ObsoleteStructWildcard);
 2678              }
 2679              if etc {
 2680                  self.bump();
 2681                  if self.token != token::RBRACE {
 2682                      let token_str = self.this_token_to_str();
 2683                      self.fatal(format!("expected `\\}`, found `{}`",
 2684                                         token_str))
 2685                  }
 2686                  etc = true;
 2687                  break;
 2688              }
 2689  
 2690              let bind_type = if self.eat_keyword(keywords::Mut) {
 2691                  BindByValue(MutMutable)
 2692              } else if self.eat_keyword(keywords::Ref) {
 2693                  BindByRef(self.parse_mutability())
 2694              } else {
 2695                  BindByValue(MutImmutable)
 2696              };
 2697  
 2698              let fieldname = self.parse_ident();
 2699  
 2700              let subpat = if self.token == token::COLON {
 2701                  match bind_type {
 2702                      BindByRef(..) | BindByValue(MutMutable) => {
 2703                          let token_str = self.this_token_to_str();
 2704                          self.fatal(format!("unexpected `{}`", token_str))
 2705                      }
 2706                      _ => {}
 2707                  }
 2708  
 2709                  self.bump();
 2710                  self.parse_pat()
 2711              } else {
 2712                  let fieldpath = ast_util::ident_to_path(self.last_span,
 2713                                                          fieldname);
 2714                  @ast::Pat {
 2715                      id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2716                      node: PatIdent(bind_type, fieldpath, None),
 2717                      span: self.last_span
 2718                  }
 2719              };
 2720              fields.push(ast::FieldPat { ident: fieldname, pat: subpat });
 2721          }
 2722          return (fields, etc);
 2723      }
 2724  
 2725      // parse a pattern.
 2726      pub fn parse_pat(&mut self) -> @Pat {
 2727          maybe_whole!(self, NtPat);
 2728  
 2729          let lo = self.span.lo;
 2730          let mut hi;
 2731          let pat;
 2732          match self.token {
 2733              // parse _
 2734            token::UNDERSCORE => {
 2735              self.bump();
 2736              pat = PatWild;
 2737              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2738              return @ast::Pat {
 2739                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2740                  node: pat,
 2741                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2742              }
 2743            }
 2744            // parse @pat
 2745            token::AT => {
 2746              self.bump();
 2747              let sub = self.parse_pat();
 2748              self.obsolete(self.span, ObsoleteManagedPattern);
 2749              let hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2750              return @ast::Pat {
 2751                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2752                  node: PatUniq(sub),
 2753                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2754              }
 2755            }
 2756            token::TILDE => {
 2757              // parse ~pat
 2758              self.bump();
 2759              let sub = self.parse_pat();
 2760              pat = PatUniq(sub);
 2761              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2762              return @ast::Pat {
 2763                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2764                  node: pat,
 2765                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2766              }
 2767            }
 2768            token::BINOP(token::AND) | token::ANDAND => {
 2769                // parse &pat
 2770                let lo = self.span.lo;
 2771                self.expect_and();
 2772                let sub = self.parse_pat();
 2773                hi = sub.span.hi;
 2774                // HACK: parse &"..." as a literal of a borrowed str
 2775                pat = match sub.node {
 2776                    PatLit(e) => {
 2777                        match e.node {
 2778                          ExprLit(lit) if lit_is_str(lit) => {
 2779                            let vst = @Expr {
 2780                                id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2781                                node: ExprVstore(e, ExprVstoreSlice),
 2782                                span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2783                            };
 2784                            PatLit(vst)
 2785                          }
 2786                          _ => PatRegion(sub),
 2787                        }
 2788                    }
 2789                    _ => PatRegion(sub),
 2790              };
 2791              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2792              return @ast::Pat {
 2793                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2794                  node: pat,
 2795                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2796              }
 2797            }
 2798            token::LPAREN => {
 2799              // parse (pat,pat,pat,...) as tuple
 2800              self.bump();
 2801              if self.token == token::RPAREN {
 2802                  hi = self.span.hi;
 2803                  self.bump();
 2804                  let lit = @codemap::Spanned {
 2805                      node: LitNil,
 2806                      span: mk_sp(lo, hi)};
 2807                  let expr = self.mk_expr(lo, hi, ExprLit(lit));
 2808                  pat = PatLit(expr);
 2809              } else {
 2810                  let mut fields = vec!(self.parse_pat());
 2811                  if self.look_ahead(1, |t| *t != token::RPAREN) {
 2812                      while self.token == token::COMMA {
 2813                          self.bump();
 2814                          if self.token == token::RPAREN { break; }
 2815                          fields.push(self.parse_pat());
 2816                      }
 2817                  }
 2818                  if fields.len() == 1 { self.expect(&token::COMMA); }
 2819                  self.expect(&token::RPAREN);
 2820                  pat = PatTup(fields);
 2821              }
 2822              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2823              return @ast::Pat {
 2824                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2825                  node: pat,
 2826                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2827              }
 2828            }
 2829            token::LBRACKET => {
 2830              // parse [pat,pat,...] as vector pattern
 2831              self.bump();
 2832              let (before, slice, after) =
 2833                  self.parse_pat_vec_elements();
 2834  
 2835              self.expect(&token::RBRACKET);
 2836              pat = ast::PatVec(before, slice, after);
 2837              hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2838              return @ast::Pat {
 2839                  id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2840                  node: pat,
 2841                  span: mk_sp(lo, hi)
 2842              }
 2843            }
 2844            _ => {}
 2845          }
 2846  
 2847          if !is_ident_or_path(&self.token)
 2848                  || self.is_keyword(keywords::True)
 2849                  || self.is_keyword(keywords::False) {
 2850              // Parse an expression pattern or exp .. exp.
 2851              //
 2852              // These expressions are limited to literals (possibly
 2853              // preceded by unary-minus) or identifiers.
 2854              let val = self.parse_literal_maybe_minus();
 2855              if self.eat(&token::DOTDOT) {
 2856                  let end = if is_ident_or_path(&self.token) {
 2857                      let path = self.parse_path(LifetimeAndTypesWithColons)
 2858                                     .path;
 2859                      let hi = self.span.hi;
 2860                      self.mk_expr(lo, hi, ExprPath(path))
 2861                  } else {
 2862                      self.parse_literal_maybe_minus()
 2863                  };
 2864                  pat = PatRange(val, end);
 2865              } else {
 2866                  pat = PatLit(val);
 2867              }
 2868          } else if self.eat_keyword(keywords::Mut) {
 2869              pat = self.parse_pat_ident(BindByValue(MutMutable));
 2870          } else if self.eat_keyword(keywords::Ref) {
 2871              // parse ref pat
 2872              let mutbl = self.parse_mutability();
 2873              pat = self.parse_pat_ident(BindByRef(mutbl));
 2874          } else {
 2875              let can_be_enum_or_struct = self.look_ahead(1, |t| {
 2876                  match *t {
 2877                      token::LPAREN | token::LBRACKET | token::LT |
 2878                      token::LBRACE | token::MOD_SEP => true,
 2879                      _ => false,
 2880                  }
 2881              });
 2882  
 2883              if self.look_ahead(1, |t| *t == token::DOTDOT) {
 2884                  let start = self.parse_expr_res(RESTRICT_NO_BAR_OP);
 2885                  self.eat(&token::DOTDOT);
 2886                  let end = self.parse_expr_res(RESTRICT_NO_BAR_OP);
 2887                  pat = PatRange(start, end);
 2888              } else if is_plain_ident(&self.token) && !can_be_enum_or_struct {
 2889                  let name = self.parse_path(NoTypesAllowed).path;
 2890                  let sub;
 2891                  if self.eat(&token::AT) {
 2892                      // parse foo @ pat
 2893                      sub = Some(self.parse_pat());
 2894                  } else {
 2895                      // or just foo
 2896                      sub = None;
 2897                  }
 2898                  pat = PatIdent(BindByValue(MutImmutable), name, sub);
 2899              } else {
 2900                  // parse an enum pat
 2901                  let enum_path = self.parse_path(LifetimeAndTypesWithColons)
 2902                                      .path;
 2903                  match self.token {
 2904                      token::LBRACE => {
 2905                          self.bump();
 2906                          let (fields, etc) =
 2907                              self.parse_pat_fields();
 2908                          self.bump();
 2909                          pat = PatStruct(enum_path, fields, etc);
 2910                      }
 2911                      _ => {
 2912                          let mut args: Vec<@Pat> = Vec::new();
 2913                          match self.token {
 2914                            token::LPAREN => {
 2915                              let is_star = self.look_ahead(1, |t| {
 2916                                  match *t {
 2917                                      token::BINOP(token::STAR) => true,
 2918                                      _ => false,
 2919                                  }
 2920                              });
 2921                              let is_dotdot = self.look_ahead(1, |t| {
 2922                                  match *t {
 2923                                      token::DOTDOT => true,
 2924                                      _ => false,
 2925                                  }
 2926                              });
 2927                              if is_star | is_dotdot {
 2928                                  // This is a "top constructor only" pat
 2929                                  self.bump();
 2930                                  if is_star {
 2931                                      self.obsolete(self.span, ObsoleteEnumWildcard);
 2932                                  }
 2933                                  self.bump();
 2934                                  self.expect(&token::RPAREN);
 2935                                  pat = PatEnum(enum_path, None);
 2936                              } else {
 2937                                  args = self.parse_enum_variant_seq(
 2938                                      &token::LPAREN,
 2939                                      &token::RPAREN,
 2940                                      seq_sep_trailing_disallowed(token::COMMA),
 2941                                      |p| p.parse_pat()
 2942                                  );
 2943                                  pat = PatEnum(enum_path, Some(args));
 2944                              }
 2945                            },
 2946                            _ => {
 2947                                if enum_path.segments.len() == 1 {
 2948                                    // it could still be either an enum
 2949                                    // or an identifier pattern, resolve
 2950                                    // will sort it out:
 2951                                    pat = PatIdent(BindByValue(MutImmutable),
 2952                                                    enum_path,
 2953                                                    None);
 2954                                } else {
 2955                                    pat = PatEnum(enum_path, Some(args));
 2956                                }
 2957                            }
 2958                          }
 2959                      }
 2960                  }
 2961              }
 2962          }
 2963          hi = self.last_span.hi;
 2964          @ast::Pat {
 2965              id: ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID,
 2966              node: pat,
 2967              span: mk_sp(lo, hi),
 2968          }
 2969      }
 2970  
 2971      // parse ident or ident @ pat
 2972      // used by the copy foo and ref foo patterns to give a good
 2973      // error message when parsing mistakes like ref foo(a,b)
 2974      fn parse_pat_ident(&mut self,
 2975                         binding_mode: ast::BindingMode)
 2976                         -> ast::Pat_ {
 2977          if !is_plain_ident(&self.token) {
 2978              self.span_fatal(self.last_span,
 2979                              "expected identifier, found path");
 2980          }

 2982          let name = self.parse_path(NoTypesAllowed).path;
 2983          let sub = if self.eat(&token::AT) {
 2984              Some(self.parse_pat())
 2985          } else {
 2986              None
 2987          };
 2988  
 2989          // just to be friendly, if they write something like
 2990          //   ref Some(i)

 2992          // leads to a parse error.  Note that if there is no explicit
 2993          // binding mode then we do not end up here, because the lookahead
 2994          // will direct us over to parse_enum_variant()

 2996              self.span_fatal(
 2997                  self.last_span,
 2998                  "expected identifier, found enum pattern");
 2999          }
 3000  
 3001          PatIdent(binding_mode, name, sub)
 3002      }

 3004      // parse a local variable declaration

 3025      // parse a "let" stmt
 3026      fn parse_let(&mut self) -> @Decl {

 3028          let local = self.parse_local();

 3030              let _ = self.parse_local();
 3031              self.obsolete(self.span, ObsoleteMultipleLocalDecl);

 3036      // parse a structure field
 3037      fn parse_name_and_ty(&mut self, pr: Visibility,
 3038                           attrs: Vec<Attribute> ) -> StructField {
 3039          let lo = self.span.lo;
 3040          if !is_plain_ident(&self.token) {

 4718      pub fn parse_item(&mut self, attrs: Vec<Attribute> ) -> Option<@Item> {

 4734  
 4735      // matches view_path : MOD? IDENT EQ non_global_path
 4736      // | MOD? non_global_path MOD_SEP LBRACE RBRACE
 4737      // | MOD? non_global_path MOD_SEP LBRACE ident_seq RBRACE
 4738      // | MOD? non_global_path MOD_SEP STAR
 4739      // | MOD? non_global_path

 4742

 4744              // use {foo,bar}

 4746                  &token::LBRACE, &token::RBRACE,
 4747                  seq_sep_trailing_allowed(token::COMMA),
 4748                  |p| p.parse_path_list_ident());

 4750                  span: mk_sp(lo, self.span.hi),
 4751                  global: false,
 4752                  segments: Vec::new()

 4755                              ViewPathList(path, idents, ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID));
 4756          }
 4757  
 4758          let first_ident = self.parse_ident();
 4759          let mut path = vec!(first_ident);
 4760          match self.token {
 4761            token::EQ => {
 4762              // x = foo::bar
 4763              self.bump();

 4765              path = vec!(self.parse_ident());
 4766              while self.token == token::MOD_SEP {
 4767                  self.bump();

 4771              let path = ast::Path {
 4772                  span: mk_sp(path_lo, self.span.hi),
 4773                  global: false,
 4774                  segments: path.move_iter().map(|identifier| {
 4775                      ast::PathSegment {
 4776                          identifier: identifier,
 4777                          lifetimes: Vec::new(),
 4778                          types: OwnedSlice::empty(),
 4779                      }
 4780                  }).collect()

 4783                              ViewPathSimple(first_ident, path,
 4784                                             ast::DUMMY_NODE_ID));

 4786  
 4787            token::MOD_SEP => {
 4788              // foo::bar or foo::{a,b,c} or foo::*
 4789              while self.token == token::MOD_SEP {

 4793                    token::IDENT(i, _) => {
